  <text>
    <body>
      <pb n="1" />
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <date>June 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 3</date>
          </dateline>
          <salute>Dear <persName ref="#stillma">Mary</persName>:</salute>
        </opener>
        <p>Your letter of the 13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi><lb/> inst. came duly to hand and gave me<lb/> great pleasure to hear from you, as you<lb/> had been mute for a long time.</p>
        <p>
	        My hands are always full of work,<lb/> so much so that it is not always convenient<lb/> for me to write a social letter.<lb/> It seems to me that I did write to you<lb/> however in March or April and got no<lb/> answer. You know that I am<lb/> publishing my book now all alone<lb/> and I am happy to say that the sales<lb/> are daily increasing. I am decidedly<lb/> rejoiced that I have the work all<lb/> in my own hands. I have over 40<lb/> agents at work and could find <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">territory</unclear><lb/> for one thousand, if I could<lb/> get so many.
        </p>
        <p>
          I will send you a copy of<lb/> the <title>New National Era</title>. (<persName ref="#douglassfr">Douglass</persName> paper<supplied resp="#fg">)</supplied><lb/> in which you will find an article<lb/> on the Underground Rail Road. The<lb/> allusion to <placeName>Burlington County</placeName>, in my article<lb/> refers to “<persName ref="#stillca">Katie Still</persName>.” (She prefers <persName ref="#stillca">Katie</persName> to Catharine)<lb/> but the <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">types</unclear> have got her initials wrong.
    <pb n="2"/>
	        <persName ref="#stillca">Catharine</persName> is quite <add place="above" rend="carrot">a</add> marked character<lb/> in <placeName>Burlington County</placeName>, and is highly<lb/> respected by the white people especially.<lb/> Her mother is something better <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">than</unclear><lb/> she was a year or two past. <persName ref="#stillpe1">Peter</persName> is<lb/> still farming and is doing about as he<lb/> formerly has been doing. I was up to <placeName>Cross<lb/> Roads</placeName> a few weeks ago and saw all the <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">folks there</unclear>.<lb/> <persName ref="#stillmat">Mahalah</persName> &amp; <persName>Gabriel</persName> are feeling the infirmities<lb/> of age &amp; so is <persName>Wesley</persName>. Indeed <persName ref="#stillja">James</persName> complains<lb/> also but the rest all seemed well. <persName ref="#stillja">James</persName><lb/> is full of practice and is making money.<lb/> His girls are trying to do something in their<lb/> way. <persName>Belinda</persName> was down to see us this<lb/> spring. Through the winter she has had<lb/> rheumatism pretty seriously, but was<lb/> recovering when here.
        </p>
        <p>
	        Poor <persName ref="#stillkiw">Kitty</persName> does not see <persName ref="#stillja">James</persName> paid<lb/> one hundred and fifty to have an<lb/> <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">operation</unclear> performed upon her eyes but as<lb/> yet nothing has been effected nor is there<lb/> any hope in this world. Yet she is just<lb/> as cheerful as ever she was and seems to<lb/> be getting on comfortably. I offered her a home<lb/> but she declined preferring to be with her children.<lb/> I allow her $4 per month regularly.</p>
        <p>
          <add place="top-left" rend="vertical">My family are<lb/> all well and<lb/> all of them<lb/> join in sending<lb/> their love to<lb/> you</add>
        </p>
        <closer rend="top-left, vertical">
          <salute>Your affec. Bro.</salute>
          <signed><persName ref="#stillwi"><choice><abbr>W</abbr><expan>William </expan></choice> Still</persName></signed>
        </closer>
    </body>
